SUMMARY:Junior Teen Idea Club
DESCRIPTION:What is a Junior Teen Idea Club? Middle School students: you are invited to gather in the teen area of the library with your friends\, eat some snacks\, and share your interests. Help US to create exciting programs and events just for YOU. Monthly meetings will be on third Thursdays right after early release from school. The program will be a combination of hanging out\, fun crafts\, games\, brainstorming\, and talking about books. This NEW program is designed to give you a chance to make the library everything you want it to be. \nThis program is free\, with no registration required. The Lake Oswego Public Library is located at 706 Fourth Street\, Lake Oswego. For more information\, contact the Youth & Teen Services Librarians at 503-697-6580 or lochild@lakeoswego.city(link sends e-mail). \nEditor’s note: This event is a community submission.
URL:https://pdxparent.com/event-single/junior-teen-idea-club/2026-03-19/
LOCATION:Lake Oswego Public Library\, 706 4th St.\, Lake Oswego\, OR\, 97034
CATEGORIES:Arts/Crafts,Books/Library,Gaming,Kids Calendar
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://pdxparent.com/wp-content/uploads/Junior-TIC-updated-PRIG.png
